deliverable_content.plan_name: Pre-Landfall Resource Allocation & Evacuation Plan (PRAEP) - Hurricane Cormorant

command_structure.framework: A Unified Command Group (UCG) will be established, co-chaired by FEMA and the State of Calusa. All interstate resource requests and operational directives will be coordinated through the UCG. The Calusa National Guard will operate under a federally-funded Title 32 status, with the Commanding General serving as a Dual-Status Commander, reporting to the Governor for state missions and the President (through the UCG) for federal missions.

allocations.description: Funds for public transportation, establishment and management of public shelters, public communications, and procurement of essential supplies (food, water, cots).
Funds allocated for securing loose shipping containers ($8M) and reinforcing hazardous material storage, specifically chlorine tanks ($2M).

A contingency fund for emergent, life-saving operational needs. Expenditures require dual-key approval from the FEMA Director and the Governor's Office. This includes the pre-approved $1M contract for LogiCore Solutions.

allocations.agency: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
allocations.description: Procurement and pre-staging of medical shelter kits, sanitation supplies, and assets to maintain the vaccine cold-chain.

budget_allocation.oversight_note: All expenditures over $250,000 require final sign-off from the FEMA representative within the Unified Command Group to ensure compliance with federal aid regulations.

assignments.description: Support traffic control points, provide security for shelters, and assist in civilian evacuation efforts as directed by the UCG.
Provide a security cordon around critical infrastructure and assist port authorities with lockdown procedures.
Augment base security forces to protect critical national security assets, operating under the UCG command structure.

assignments.role: Lead Unified Command Group, manage federal resource integration, and oversee financial disbursement.
Establish public health monitoring in shelters and advise on sanitation protocols.

assignments.task: Transport and maintain cold-chain for medical supplies under CDC direction.
Assigned to the FEMA Operational Reserve for flexible deployment to meet emergent logistical needs as directed by the UCG.
Ensure command and control continuity for all agencies operating under the UCG.
Pre-positioned outside the immediate impact zone for rapid post-landfall deployment.
Provide potable water support to municipal shelters post-landfall as directed by the UCG.
